<section id="contributing" class="px-6 py-24 lg:py-32">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl">
    <div class="mb-16 text-center">
      <p class="mb-4 text-sm font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-accent">
        Build With InferNode
      </p>
      <h2 class="mb-6 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
        The API is a filesystem.<br />Use any language.
      </h2>
      <p class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-lg text-text-muted">
        There is no SDK. There is no client library. If your language can read and write
        files, it can talk to InferNode. The 9P protocol turns every resource into a
        filesystem&mdash;and every language already knows how to use files.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Language examples -->
    <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">

      <!-- Python -->
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface overflow-hidden">
        <div class="border-b border-border px-4 py-2">
          <span class="text-xs font-medium text-node-llm">Python</span>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 font-mono text-xs leading-relaxed">
          <div class="text-text-muted"># Query an LLM via InferNode</div>
          <div><span class="text-node-cloud">with</span> <span class="text-text">open</span>(<span class="text-node-jetson">"/n/llm/prompt"</span>, <span class="text-node-jetson">"w"</span>) <span class="text-node-cloud">as</span> f:</div>
          <div class="pl-4">f.write(<span class="text-node-jetson">"Summarise this report"</span>)</div>
          <div class="mt-2"><span class="text-node-cloud">with</span> <span class="text-text">open</span>(<span class="text-node-jetson">"/n/llm/response"</span>) <span class="text-node-cloud">as</span> f:</div>
          <div class="pl-4">answer = f.read()</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Go -->
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface overflow-hidden">
        <div class="border-b border-border px-4 py-2">
          <span class="text-xs font-medium text-node-jetson">Go</span>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 font-mono text-xs leading-relaxed">
          <div class="text-text-muted">// Read a sensor feed</div>
          <div>data, err := os.ReadFile(</div>
          <div class="pl-4"><span class="text-node-jetson">"/n/sensors/temperature"</span>)</div>
          <div class="mt-2"><span class="text-text-muted">// Write a command</span></div>
          <div>os.WriteFile(</div>
          <div class="pl-4"><span class="text-node-jetson">"/n/actuator/valve"</span>,</div>
          <div class="pl-4">[]byte(<span class="text-node-jetson">"open"</span>), 0644)</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Bash -->
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface overflow-hidden">
        <div class="border-b border-border px-4 py-2">
          <span class="text-xs font-medium text-node-rpi">Bash</span>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 font-mono text-xs leading-relaxed">
          <div class="text-text-muted"># List available tools</div>
          <div><span class="text-node-laptop">ls</span> /n/agent/tools/</div>
          <div class="mt-2"><span class="text-text-muted"># Send a task to an agent</span></div>
          <div><span class="text-node-laptop">echo</span> <span class="text-node-jetson">"find anomalies"</span> \</div>
          <div class="pl-4">> /n/agent/task</div>
          <div class="mt-2"><span class="text-text-muted"># Read the result</span></div>
          <div><span class="text-node-laptop">cat</span> /n/agent/result</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- The point -->
    <div class="mx-auto mt-10 max-w-3xl rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface p-8">
      <div class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-2">
        <div>
          <h3 class="mb-3 font-semibold">No SDK. No bindings. No lock-in.</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
            Every InferNode resource&mdash;LLMs, sensors, agents, tools, databases&mdash;is
            exposed as files via the 9P protocol. You interact with them using standard file
            operations in whatever language you already use. Write an integration in Python,
            Go, Rust, C, JavaScript, Bash, or anything else. If it can <code class="text-accent font-mono text-xs">open()</code> a file, it works.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="mb-3 font-semibold">Contribute without learning Limbo.</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
            InferNode is written in Limbo and C, but you don&rsquo;t need to know either to
            build on it. Write your integration in your language. Mount it via 9P. It becomes
            part of the namespace&mdash;indistinguishable from a native service. The filesystem
            <em>is</em> the interface contract.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="mt-10 text-center">
      <a
        href="https://github.com/NERVsystems/infernode"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg border border-border px-6 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-text-muted transition hover:border-accent hover:text-text"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
      >
        Explore the source on GitHub &rarr;
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
